    "# 🎯 Probability Bowl Model — World Cup 2026\n",
    "**Brier-score optimized. Market-first. Dixon-Coles corrected. Historical data backed.**\n",
    "\n",
    "### Data sources\n",
    "- **martj42/international_results** — 49K+ international results (CC0, free)\n",
    "- **BSD API** — live odds, lineups, suspensions (free, no key needed for basic use)\n",
    "- **football-data.org** — WC 2026 fixtures (free tier)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Pipeline\n",
    "```\n",
    "Historical rates (martj42)\n",
    "        +\n",
    "Market odds (BSD/bookmakers)     →  λ estimation  →  Dixon-Coles  →  300K Monte Carlo  →  Props\n",
    "        +\n",
    "Lineups / suspensions (BSD)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### How to use\n",
    "1. Run **Cells 1-5** once per session (setup)\n",
    "2. For each match: fill in **Cell 6** (odds + context) and run\n",
    "3. For player props: fill in **Cell 7** and run\n",
    "4. Compare output to crowd — diverge only where you have a reason"
   ]
